IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: FORGING STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIPS FOR ECONOMIC GROWTH.
IRS990.MissionDesc: WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT BOARD OF SOUTH CENTRAL WISCONSIN, INC.'S MISSION IS TO BUILD PUBLIC AND PRIVATE PARTNERSHIPS THAT SUPPORT INNOVATION AND EXCELLENCE IN WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT.IN FURTHERANCE OF ITS MISSION THE ORGANIZATION DEDICATES TIME, TALENT AND FINANCIAL RESOURCES TO: PROMOTING ECONOMIC OPPORTUNITIES FOR THE WORKFORCE; TARGETING DISADVANTAGED AND DISLOCATED WORKERS; ALLOCATING RESOURCES EQUITABLY THROUGHOUT THE REGION; RESPONDING TO LOCAL NEEDS; SUPPORTING A CUSTOMER DRIVEN SYSTEM; MAINTAINING FISCAL INTEGRITY.
IRS990.Desc: WORKFORCE INNOVATION AND OPPORTUNITY ACT (WIOA) ADULT AND DISLOCATED WORKERS PROGRAMS SEEK TO IMPROVE EMPLOYMENT, RETENTION, AND EARNINGS OF WIOA PARTICIPANTS AND INCREASE THEIR EDUCATIONAL AND OCCUPATIONAL SKILL ATTAINMENT, THEREBY IMPROVING THE QUALITY OF THE WORKFORCE, REDUCING WELFARE DEPENDENCY, AND ENHANCING NATIONAL PRODUCTIVITY AND COMPETITIVENESS. ON THE JOB TRAINING (OJT) PROGRAM IS A TRAINING STRATEGY GEARED TOWARD LOCAL EMPLOYERS AND JOB SEEKERS TO PUT DISLOCATED WORKERS BACK TO WORK EARNING A WAGE WHILE RECEIVING TRAINING. IN FISCAL YEAR 2018 THIS PROGRAM SERVED 912 PARTICIPANTS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: YOUTH ACTIVITIES SEEK TO INCREASE THE ATTAINMENT OF BASIC SKILLS, WORK READINESS, OR OCCUPATIONAL SKILLS, AND SECONDARY DIPLOMAS OR OTHER CREDENTIALS. A PERSON IS ELIGIBLE TO RECEIVE SERVICES UNDER YOUTH ACTIVITIES IF THEY ARE BETWEEN THE AGES OF FOURTEEN AND TWENTY-ONE AT THE TIME OF ENROLLMENT AND DEMONSTRATE AT LEAST ONE OF THE FOLLOWING BARRIERS TO EMPLOYMENT: DEFICIENT IN BASIC LITERACY SKILLS, A SCHOOL DROPOUT, HOMELESS, A RUNAWAY, A FOSTER CHILD, PREGNANT OR PARENTING, OFFENDER, OR AN INDIVIDUAL WHO REQUIRES ADDITIONAL ASSISTANCE TO COMPLETE AN EDUCATIONAL PROGRAM OR TO SECURE AND HOLD EMPLOYMENT. THE ORGANIZATION SERVED APPROXIMATELY 377 PARTICIPANTS IN YOUTH ACTIVITIES DURING THE YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: THE ORGANIZATION'S SPECIAL PROJECTS THAT FOCUS ON SPECIFIC OBJECTIVES AND/OR TARGET POPULATIONS. THESE PROGRAMS INCLUDE THE LEAP AND WINDOWS TO WORK PROGRAM, WHICH PROVIDES CASE MANAGEMENT SERVICES TO HELP PARTICIPANTS SEARCH FOR AND SECURE EMPLOYMENT TO ENSURE SUCCESSFUL REINTEGRATION INTO THE COMMUNITY AFTER RELEASE. OTHER SPECIAL PROJECTS ALSO INCLUDE LOCAL YOUTH APPRENTICESHIP, AS WELL AS PRE-APPRENTICESHIP AND REGISTERED APPRENTICESHIP WORK. THE ORGANIZATION SERVED 647 PARTICIPANTS THROUGH SPECIAL PROJECTS DURING THE YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: INDEPENDENT LIVING PROGRAM SEEKS TO ENGAGE A NETWORK OF SERVICE RESOURCES TO MEET THE TRANSITION NEEDS OF YOUNG PEOPLE EXITING FOSTER CARE AND TRANSITIOING INTO ADULT LIVING. THE SUPPORTS AND SERVICES ARE DESIGNED TO HELP ELIGIBLE YOUTH COMPLETE HIGH SCHOOL, TRANSITION TO POST SECONDARY EDUCATION, OR TO OBTAIN AND MAINTAIN EMPLOYMENT AND BASIC NEEDS. THE ORGAIZATION SERVED 121 YOUNG ADULTS IN THE REGION DURING THE PROGRAM YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS REQUIRED TO ASSESS WHETHER IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT A TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION ASSUMING THE TAXING AUTHORITY HAS FULL KNOWLEDGE OF ALL INFORMATION. IF THE TAX POSITION DOES NOT MEET THE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT RECOGNITION THRESHOLD, THE BENEFIT OF THAT POSITION IS NOT RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATION HAS DETERMINED THERE ARE NO AMOUNTS TO RECORD AS ASSETS OR LIABILITIES RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: ASSISTANCE FOR TUITION, BOOKS, AND OTHER CAREER ASSISTANCE

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PROCEDURES TO MONITOR THE USE OF GRANTS INCLUDE ON-SITE MONITORING VISITS DURING THE YEAR, REVIEW OF ANNUAL AUDIT REPORTS OF THE GRANTEES, AND CONSTANT COMMUNICATION WITH GRANTEES. ON-SITE VISITS INCLUDE REVIEWS OF FILES AND ARE COMPARED WITH INFORMATION ENTERED IN THE SHARED DATABASE, PROCEDURAL REVIEWS AND DISCUSSIONS WITH MANAGEMENT. PROGRAM PERSONNEL REVIEW ACTIVITY OF THE GRANT RECIPIENTS ON AN ON-GOING BASIS BY REVIEWING ACTIVITY IN THE SHARED DATABASE AND REVIEW OF VARIOUS FINANCIAL AND PROGRAM REPORTS REQUIRED OF THE GRANTEES. GRANTS TO INDIVIDUALS REQUIRE AUTHORIZATION BY CASE MANAGERS AND SUPPORTING DOCUMENTATION PRIOR TO PAYMENT BEING MADE. THERE ARE A LARGE AMOUNT OF GRANTS TO INDIVIDUALS THAT ARE TO PAY FOR TUITION AND BOOKS, THESE ARE NORMALLY PAID DIRECTLY TO THE INSTITUTION AND THE ORGANIZATION IS LISTED ON ACCOUNT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE RETURN IS PROVIDED TO THE FINANCE DIRECTOR AND CEO/EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR FOR REVIEW. IN TURN, THE DRAFT IS THEN PROVIDED TO MEMBERS OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE, WHICH CONSISTS OF VOTING MEMBERS, FOR REVIEW BEFORE FILING WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, KEY EMPLOYEES, AND EMPLOYEES OF WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT BOARD OF SOUTH CENTRAL WISCONSIN ARE COVERED UNDER THE ORGANIZATION'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, KEY EMPLOYEES, AND EMPLOYEES ARE TO DISCLOSE INTEREST THAT MAY LEAD TO A CONFLICT AND ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT ANNUALLY. THE INTERESTED PARTY MUST FULLY DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND COMPLETELY RECUSE HIM/HERSELF FROM THE DISCUSSION AND ANY RELATED VOTE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE ANNUALLY CONDUCTS AN EVALUATION OF THE CEO/EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND APPROVES COMPENSATION AS PART OF THE ANNUAL BUDGET PROCESS WHICH REQUIRES A VOTE OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE. THE BOARD HAS UTILIZED SALARY SURVEY INFORMATION COMPILED BY THE STATE OF WISCONSIN SPECIALLY FOR WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT BOARD KEY EMPLOYEES. THIS STUDY WAS LAST CONDUCTED IN 2017. THE CEO/EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR FOLLOWS THE SAME PROCESS FOR THE OTHER EXECUTIVE POSITIONS WITHIN THE ORGANIZATION. A VOTE BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS REQUIRED FOR ALL COMPENSATION INCLUDED WITHIN THE CORPORATE BUDGET.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
